The paper deals with adversarial attacks in computer vision tasks such as image captioning and image segmentation, which are typically categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a task-agnostic approach, which involves using a feature extractor, a common technique in machine learning and deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which is a topic of interest in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves generating natural-looking adversarial images, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
